{"word":"H4864 - מַשְׂאֵת - masʼêth - mas-ayth' - Burden","slug":"H4864","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מַשְׂאֵת</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>masʼêth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mas-ayth'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Burden"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05D0;&#x05EA; - mas&#x0301;'e&#x0302;th</b> - <i>mas-ayth'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H5375\">H5375</a>; properly (abstractly) a <i>raising</i> (as of the hands in prayer), or <i>rising</i> (of flame); figuratively an <i>utterance</i>; concretely a <i>beacon</i> (as <i>raised</i>); a <i>present</i> (as taken), <i>mess</i>, or <i>tribute</i>; figuratively a <i>reproach</i> (as a burden): - burden, collection, sign of fire, (great) flame, gift, lifting up, mess, oblation, reward."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4853\">H4853</a>, <a href=\"#/H4856\">H4856</a>, <a href=\"#/H4858\">H4858</a>, <a href=\"#/H4984\">H4984</a>, <a href=\"#/H5375\">H5375</a>, <a href=\"#/H5379\">H5379</a>, <a href=\"#/H5385\">H5385</a>, <a href=\"#/H5387\">H5387</a>, <a href=\"#/H7613\">H7613</a>, <a href=\"#/H7721\">H7721</a>, <a href=\"#/H7863\">H7863</a>, <a href=\"#/H7865\">H7865</a>"}]}